/-
  Ripple.LPP.EhrenfestUrn — Generalized Ehrenfest Urns

  Formalizes the model from:
    M. Albenque and L. Gerin, "On the algebraic numbers computable by some
    generalized Ehrenfest urns," DMTCS 14(2):271–284, 2012.  (arXiv:1104.5643)

  An Ehrenfest urn with rule (k, f) draws k balls at each step, examines
  the count j of black balls among them, and recolors all k to f(j).
  In the large-population limit, the proportion of black balls follows
  the mean-field ODE dx/dt = b(x), where b is the drift polynomial:

    b(y) = k · Σ_{j∈E_f} C(k,j) y^j (1-y)^{k-j} − k·y

  The Ehrenfest model is a restricted subclass of LPP: 2 states (binary),
  k-way interactions. Its computable set L satisfies (Theorem 5):
    - L is symmetric about 1/2
    - L is dense in [0,1]
    - L contains algebraic numbers of every degree d ≥ 1
    - L contains exactly five rationals: {0, 1/3, 1/2, 2/3, 1}
-/

